&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Redwood Materials&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Redwood is localizing a global battery supply chain that seamlessly integrates recovery, reuse, and recycling&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;—&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;keeping critical minerals in circulation and driving the energy transition. Founded in 2017,&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;we’re delivering low-cost and large-scale energy storage and producing battery materials in the U.S. for the first time, all from batteries we already have.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a self-motivated, proactive, and detail-oriented Analytical Laboratory Technician II to join our growing startup team. This role is split between executing daily routine analysis to support CAM1 Production and advancing CAM R&amp;amp;D initiatives. As a crucial bridge in our operations, you will coordinate directly with CAM1 operators and R&amp;amp;D scientists to resolve technical questions and ensure data accuracy. Beyond benchmark, you will take ownership of daily lab functionality, manage inventory, and troubleshoot instrumentation. Because we operate in a fast-paced startup environment, the ideal candidate is a natural multi-tasker who anticipates team needs and steps in to help without being asked.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities will include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform daily routine chemical and physical analysis to support CAM1 production quality control and CAM R&amp;amp;D projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strictly adhere to Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs), safety regulations, and CAM lab compliance requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Efficiently multi-task between high-volume sample analysis, regular lab maintenance, and non-laboratory supporting tasks as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a key point of contact, communicating and coordinating effectively with CAM1 Operators and CAM R&amp;amp;D Scientists regarding sample status, data discrepancies, or technical questions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver clear, accurate, and timely data reports to cross-functional teams to ensure production and research timelines are met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the inventory of chemicals, consumables, and general laboratory supplies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively monitor stock levels and coordinate with the Laboratory Manager to initiate restocking before shortages occur.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a clean, organized, safe, and fully functional laboratory environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate, calibrate, and maintain analytical laboratory instrumentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desired Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in science or related field or 2+ years of related experience in an analytical laboratory environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in laboratory settings, quality settings, or chemical production facilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in typical laboratory practices including waste handling, safe work practices, data entry and management, good documentation practices and experimental setup and execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable wearing personal protective equipment including but not limited to lab coats and respirators.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with relevant test methods such as ICP-OES, auto-titration, X-Ray Fluorescence, Total Organic Carbon, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
