&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Battery Disassembly Technician, Energy Storage &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The&amp;nbsp;Battery Disassembly Technician performs&amp;nbsp;safe, efficient, and high-quality disassembly of EV battery packs and modules within a high-volume manufacturing environment. The position requires strict adherence to high-voltage safety protocols, standardized work instructions, and continuous process improvement.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities will include: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform safe, controlled disassembly of EV and energy storage battery packs down to module and component level, following detailed work instructions and safety standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute high-voltage isolation, verification, and handling procedures, including strict adherence to lockout/tagout (LOTO) and PPE requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sort, classify, and route battery components for reuse, recycling, or disposal in compliance with environmental and production guidelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate within a high-throughput production environment, meeting performance targets while maintaining efficiency, accuracy, and workflow continuity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize hand tools, power tools, and electrical diagnostic equipment to support disassembly, inspection, and basic troubleshooting tasks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safely handle, transport, and lift large-format battery systems using forklifts, cranes, hoists, and rigging equipment in accordance with safety protocols&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally to support continuous improvement, maintain a safe and organized workspace, and ensure compliance with quality and EHS standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desired Qualifications: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate a variety of material handling equipment and mechanical lifts (training provided).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must meet all requirements for use of a full-face respirator, including medical clearance and fit testing,&amp;nbsp;in accordance with&amp;nbsp;OSHA and company standards.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrates working knowledge of mechanical fastening systems, electrical connections, and component-level disassembly techniques.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior rigging and heavy material handling experience&amp;nbsp;is&amp;nbsp;strongly preferred; however, training and certification will be provided for candidates with foundational mechanical aptitude.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supports field operations as&amp;nbsp;required&amp;nbsp;(up to 10% travel) for battery system decommissioning, including on-site disassembly and material recovery.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Position includes&amp;nbsp;additional&amp;nbsp;internal and external&amp;nbsp;trainings&amp;nbsp;such as LOTO,&amp;nbsp;Lifting/Rigging&amp;nbsp;and High voltage Battery Basics etc.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
